I heard that the audience usually claps for certain people every year at this event. I think one of the reasons why it's especially irking to listen to this year is because Billie has the type of voice that makes us want to remain silent and fully appreciate her performance. Especially when it's a solemn song and Billie isn't going out of her way to hype the crowd.


This is my take on it at least. I hope Billie releases a studio version of this since I can't stop listening to it over and over again.

snippet.textDisplay: Even if the Oscars made the case for not including Luke Perry cause he was mostly known for his tv roles(even though he was in a number of movies) why not include Sid Haig? He had minor appearances on Star Trek, Charlie’s Angels, The Flying Nun, and the Batman TV show just to name a few. It makes me think because he wasn’t included because he’s a horror icon and The Academy detests horror films, even though they don’t mind stealing their ideas to use for a musical number. Just flat out disrespectful.
